file=Brand Studio/weave/operational/skill/weave-skill-routing.md · h=name: weave-skill-routing\ntype: operational/skill\nstatus: consolidated from the "Boundaries" sections of weave's skill files — no new logic invented\nassigned_agent: weave (Brand Studio / Storytelling)\ndate_added: 2026-07-07\n · p:=Weave's routing map. Triggers: `operational/commands/weave-commands.md`.\n · wif:Where Identity Fits=Weave has no identity — spark holds Brand Studio's. Universal-only principles.\n · avc:Architecture vs Craft (the two-skill split)=```\nbrand-story-arcs   (ARCHITECTURE — which chapter is this, may it exist: · tb=\|             arc loaded → element advanced → ARC-FIT → continuity → verdict + ledger) · avc:Architecture vs Craft (the two-skill split)=v\nbrand-storytelling (CRAFT — how the approved chapter hooks and lands:\nfive-second moment, stakes/elephant, start-in-action,\ncustomer-as-hero, dinner-test repeatability, memification)\n```\n\nArchitecture always runs first: craft polishing an off-arc chapter is wasted craft. Craft runs inside every ON-ARC chapter before it goes to lena for wording.\n · hr:Handoff Rules=- **muse → brand-story-arcs**: surviving concepts arrive for chapter positioning; OFF-ARC verdicts return with the on-arc alternative (muse's library records both).\n- **brand-story-arcs → brand-storytelling → lena**: approved chapter → craft treatment (hook, moment, stakes) → lena's voice + humanic pass. Weave never wordsmiths final copy.\n- **→ pulse**: a chapter serializes into platform-native content; the ledger tracks chapters, pulse's calendar tracks posts. Pulse's series must map to chapters.\n- **→ spark**: arc fit is one of spark's three gate references; this skill's verdict is that check's engine. ARC GAP amendments route to the operator via spark's review.\n- **↔ echo**: the brand arc and echo's investor pitch-narrative tell the same facts to different audiences — contradictions between them are a finding for both, escalated to the operator.\n- **Behavioral Science (dormant)**: chapter framing review (kahneman attention/framing, cialdini ethics line) sits between lena's wording and spark's gate.\n · p:Precedence="Does this fit our story / what's the story here" → brand-story-arcs. "Make this story better / hook / structure" → brand-storytelling (after arc check if it's campaign-bound). "Build our story" → arc creation loop. Ambiguous → ask whether the need is positioning (architecture) or telling (craft).\n · f:=No arc → brand-story-arcs' Phase-1 stop (build from real history, or labeled pre-arc content). Craft questions with no campaign attached run brand-storytelling standalone.\n